        <h2 id="lobster-roll-recipe">Recipe #1</h2>
        
        <ul>
            <li>Time: 20 minutes</li>
            <li>Serves: 4</li>
        </ul>
        
        <table>
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Ingredients</th>
                    <th>Quantity</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <td> Lobster</td>
                <td> 4 Lobster Tails</td>
            </tbody>
            <tbody>
                <td>Mayonaise</td>
                <td>1/2 Cup</td>
            </tbody>
            <tbody>
                <td>Lemon Juice</td>
                <td>3 Tablespoons</td>
            </tbody>
            <tbody>
                <td>Inner Celery Stalks and Leaves</td>
                <td> 2 </td>
            </tbody>
            <tbody>
                <td>Chopped Parsley Leaves</td>
                <td>2 Tablespoons</td>
            </tbody>
            <tbody>
                <td>Salt and Black Pepper</td>
                <td>---</td>
            </tbody>
            <tbody>
                <td>Lightly Toasted Rolls</td>
                <td>4</td>
            </tbody>
            <tbody>
                <td>Melted Butter</td>
                <td>--- (Brushing rolls)</td>
            </tbody>
            
        </table>
        
        <p><strong>Step 1:</strong> Remove the meat from the lobster tails and cut into bite sized pieces.<br><strong>Step 2:</strong>Put in bowl with mayonaise, celery, parlesy, lemon juice, salt and pepper. Mix thourghly.<br> <strong>Step 3:</strong> Coat the rolls with the melted butter. <br> <strong>Note: Put the lobster in the fridge before (5-10 minutes) for a better taste.</strong>
</p>
        
    <p><em>Source for Recipe #1: <a href="https://www.foodnetwork.com/recipes/lobster-rolls-recipe0-1938206"><br>Lobster Roll</a></em></p>
    
